The Herald Freedom Mupanedemo – Midlands Bureau
Police in Kwekwe are investigating a suspected murder case in which a Kwekwe High School staffer was found dead with her body floating in the school’s disused swimming pool today. The now deceased, Ms Patricia Pinga (36) who was a general hand at the school, went missing on Sunday soon after knocking off from weekend duty. Her relatives made a report of a missing person to the police on Monday only for her body to be found in the school back yard today. Midlands Provincial Police Spokesperson Inspector Emmanuel Mahoko confirmed the death saying investigations were under way.